          <unittitle>Personal Photographs</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Personal Photographs series, 1897-1963, consists of photographs and postcards related to Zurel's family. The series includes a group of photographs of employees at the Wilson Automation Company in Warren, Michigan, where Zurel's father Lloyd Howard Zurel was an engineer; portraits of the Zurel family members and images of family property in Michigan. This series also includes a group of late-19th-century photos of locations in the Upper Peninsula--Ironwood and Calumet--depicting street scenes and mines. Most postcards are of Michigan towns and locations. A group of postcards depicts WWI military camp in Ohio. </p>
        </scopecontent>
